      • cleanParameters

        public void cleanParameters()
        Reset when there is only $PARAMETER selection (and no other selection) although at this moment the $PARAMETER's should be already replaced by user entered values, there are cases where the user is not prompted for parameters (for ex. filter called from dashboard) in this case the $PARAMETER value should be neglected otherwise the result will be empty If there are also other selections as $PARAMETER, then the $PARAMETER will be not removed because in SQL IN clauses it does not hurt
